cookies:
great for storing data on client, bit not for sensitive data so it isnt manipulated

cookies can be configured to expire when the browser is closed i.e session cookie or when a certain age is reached i.e permanent cookie

Works well together with Sessions

Sessions: 
stored on the server, not on the client
Great for  storing sensitive data that should survive across requests
You can Store Anything in Sessions
often used for Storing user Data/authentication status
identified via cookie
you can use differernt storages for saving your sessions on the server.